COAST SAVINGS FINANCIAL Inc., Los Angeles, said it completed an exchange offer for $52 million of 7% convertible subordinated debentures.
The debentures, due in 2011, were originally issued by Coast Savings & Loan Association, the parent company's thrift unit.
Holders of $38.5 million of the debentures, or 75% of the total outstanding, tendered them in the exchange of 54 common shares for each $1,000 of bonds.
About 2.1 million shares were involved in the exchange. 

